commit.message:
Specify right kernel commit in README

The haveged-like jitter entropy algo was added in 5.4. The 5.6 commit is
for making /dev/random never block. I kept the reference to the latter
in there too, in case it's relevant, but I'm pretty sure what you had in
mind here was the 5.4 commit.

Round bits up and target full pool size

commit.message:
Round bits up and target full pool size

Rather than rounding bits down, round them up. Otherwise 249 bits full
in a 256 bit pool won't ever get filled up with the additional 7 bits.
In addition, target a full pool rather than a half pool, since a full
pool is sometimes required.
